      "post_content": "Granted it's useless in anything but a U/R deck with a ton of draw but it really excels in that particular deck. Personally, I love it. It's an undiscovered gem for [Niv-Mizzet, The Firemind](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Niv-Mizzet, The Firemind ) EDH decks.  \n  \n[Reiterate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reiterate) + Inner Fire + 7 cards in hand (not counting reiterate) + 7RRR = infinite red mana. You can then use the bought back reiterate to reiterate pretty much any other spell for infinite damage or removal (infinite [Chaos Warp](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chaos Warp)s or [Brainstorm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainstorm)s is fun) Or just pour it into a [Comet Storm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Comet Storm) or [Conflagrate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Conflagrate).  \n  \nI do this usually by turn 4-7 on average but turn 1 is possible with certain broken blue cards which shall not be named) Barring those, [Consecrated Sphinx](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Consecrated Sphinx ) + [Wheel of Fortune](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wheel of Fortune) works quite nicely.  \n  \nWhenever I use it to get like 10 to 50 red mana I smirk as people \"ooh\" and \"aww\" because then I just reiterate or twincast it f... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
